OL,6,FAdding that had he stayed with his
OL,7,Fbirth mother, he most likely would "be
OL,8,Fwith us today".
OL,10,FLaura Corkill, Leiland-James' birth
OL,11,Fmother, said she wanted to keep her
OL,12,Fson and had made positive changes to
OL,13,Fher life in order to do so.
OL,15,FHe was taken into care by the then
OL,16,FCumbria County Council when he was 2
OL,17,Fdays old, and lived with a foster
OL,18,Ffamily for eight months before being
OL,19,Fplaced with the Castle family in .
